  "prompt": "My grandfather died recently; he owned a MacBook Air. I want to use it now but it isn't wiped, and he never wrote down his password. Can Apple help?",
  "response": "I'm sorry for your loss. Yes, Apple can help in certain situations, but there are limitations and steps you\u2019ll need to follow to gain access to your grandfather's MacBook Air. Here\u2019s what you can do:\n\n### 1. **Try to Reset the Password (If Possible)**\n   - If the MacBook Air is running macOS Recovery, you can try resetting the password using his Apple ID or recovery key:\n     1. Restart the Mac and hold **Command + R** to boot into Recovery Mode.\n     2. Open **Terminal** from the Utilities menu.\n     3. Type `resetpassword` and follow the on-screen instructions.\n   - Note: This works only if FileVault disk encryption is not enabled.\n\n### 2. **Contact Apple Support**\n   - If you can\u2019t reset the password, you\u2019ll need to contact Apple Support for assistance. Be prepared to provide:\n     - Proof of your identity (e.g., passport, driver\u2019s license).\n     - Proof of your grandfather\u2019s passing (e.g., death certificate).\n     - Proof that you are the legal beneficiary or executor of his estate (e.g., will or court documents).\n   - Apple may be able to help unlock the device or guide you through the process of wiping it and setting it up as new.\n\n### 3. **Erase and Reinstall macOS (If Necessary)**\n   - If you don\u2019t need access to the data on the MacBook Air and just want to use it, you can erase the drive and reinstall macOS:\n     1. Boot into **Recovery Mode (Command + R)**.\n     2. Open **Disk Utility** and erase the internal drive.\n     3. Exit Disk Utility and reinstall macOS from the Recovery menu.\n   - This will wipe all data on the MacBook Air, so only do this if you\u2019re sure you don\u2019t need the files.\n\n### 4. **Check for Legacy Contacts (if applicable)**\n   - If your grandfather set up a **Legacy Contact** in his Apple ID settings, that person can request access to his Apple account and devices. Learn more here: [Apple Legacy Contact](https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT212360).\n\n### 5. **Consult a Legal Professional (if Needed)**\n   - If necessary, consult a lawyer or legal professional to help you navigate the process of accessing your grandfather\u2019s estate and digital assets.\n\nApple takes privacy and security seriously, so they will require documentation to ensure you\u2019re authorized to access the device. Be patient and prepared with the necessary paperwork.",
